definition.value: A purine nucleoside having adenine as the nucleobase and a carboxy group at C-5'.
An oxoproline having the oxo group placed at the 5-position. It is an intermediate metabolite in the glutathione cycle.
A primary alcohol that is hexan-1-ol substituted by an ethyl group at position 2.
A 1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinoline hacing chloro substituents at the 7- and 8-positions.
